1
00:00:49,620 --> 00:00:53,820
=Camellias=

2
00:00:53,860 --> 00:00:56,740
=Episode 15=

3
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:58,920
Zhaohua.

4
00:00:59,479 --> 00:01:00,880
Where are you taking me?

5
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,359
Just wait a little longer,

6
00:01:03,359 --> 00:01:05,040
Your Majesty. You'll see soon.

7
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,040
We're here.

8
00:01:15,959 --> 00:01:17,920
(Stay back! Get away!)

9
00:01:19,359 --> 00:01:22,359
Isn't this the one
you've wanted dead all along?

10
00:01:22,359 --> 00:01:23,680
The things

11
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:25,680
she can do for you,

12
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,239
I can do as well.

13
00:01:29,319 --> 00:01:30,319
And over there,

14
00:01:32,519 --> 00:01:34,159
does she look familiar?

15
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,480
(Mother,)

16
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:37,319
(don't leave me!)

17
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:41,280
Today, Your Highness may do
whatever you wish with these two.

18
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,879
Zhaohua.

19
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,079
How could I

20
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:47,640
not love you?

21
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,359
Your Majesty,

22
00:01:51,079 --> 00:01:53,120
I'm feeling tired.

23
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,239
I'll take my leave now.

24
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,439
Your Majesty,

25
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:08,080
please let me go!

26
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:14,680
Your Majesty.

27
00:02:15,159 --> 00:02:16,439
We lost the battle at the front.

28
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:17,479
What?

29
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,599
Tens of thousands of Kun's finest troops

30
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,879
couldn't even defeat a few thousand
enemy soldiers?

31
00:02:21,879 --> 00:02:22,919
What good are you?

32
00:02:23,719 --> 00:02:24,759
Calm down, Your Majesty.

33
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:26,599
The enemy learned
of General Rong Xiu's death,

34
00:02:26,599 --> 00:02:28,360
so they took a detour
to burn our grain supplies.

35
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,879
Morale was shattered,

36
00:02:29,879 --> 00:02:31,599
and that falls on the commander.

37
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:32,520
Guards.

38
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,319
Take Wang Chuang into custody,

39
00:02:34,319 --> 00:02:35,400
pending sentencing.

40
00:02:35,759 --> 00:02:36,560
Mercy, Your Majesty!

41
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,120
Your Majesty!

42
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:37,520
Move!

43
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,919
I marched my troops into the city.

44
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:39,800
Along the way, the people,

45
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,199
young and old alike,
sang songs mocking you

46
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:42,400
as a tyrant.

47
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,759
But you've been kept in the dark.

48
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:44,680
The foundation of Kun

49
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:45,879
will soon be destroyed

50
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:48,360
by you, a depraved, tyrannical ruler!

51
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,000
What songs?

52
00:02:50,439 --> 00:02:51,360
Have you heard them?

53
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,560
Your Majesty,

54
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,599
I haven't heard them.

55
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,280
You haven't?

56
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:57,680
Guards.

57
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:58,120
Yes?

58
00:02:58,319 --> 00:02:59,400
Take her away and behead her.

59
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:00,719
Your Majesty,

60
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:02,120
I truly haven't heard them!

61
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:03,439
Please, Your Majesty!

62
00:03:03,599 --> 00:03:04,080
Your Majesty!

63
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:04,879
Your Majesty!

64
00:03:04,879 --> 00:03:06,199
I truly haven't heard them!

65
00:03:06,199 --> 00:03:06,840
Your Majesty!

66
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:07,879
Your Majesty!

67
00:03:08,879 --> 00:03:09,639
You,

68
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,360
have you heard them?

69
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:14,520
Speak!

70
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,240
The enchantress brings chaos
to the realm.

71
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,360
Zhu Yunqi, the cruel tyrant.

72
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,400
Nights of revelry cloud his mind.

73
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,639
Noble ladies meet their tragic end.

74
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:27,800
Harsh laws grind the people down.

75
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:30,159
Disasters strike. Hearts grow cold.

76
00:03:30,159 --> 00:03:32,400
Rise up, brave warriors,
to end this tyranny.

77
00:03:33,319 --> 00:03:34,680
A new dynasty.

78
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:35,800
A new...

79
00:03:36,439 --> 00:03:37,560
A new age.

80
00:03:39,199 --> 00:03:41,039
You know them well, don't you?

81
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,479
Guards!

82
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,120
Yes!

83
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,439
Take her away and behead her.

84
00:03:44,439 --> 00:03:45,479
No, Your Majesty!

85
00:03:45,479 --> 00:03:46,120
No!

86
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,599
Please, Your Majesty!

87
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,199
Mercy, Your Majesty!

88
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:50,159
Your Majesty!

89
00:03:50,319 --> 00:03:52,159
They're just rumors.

90
00:03:52,159 --> 00:03:54,240
No need to take them so seriously.

91
00:03:57,159 --> 00:03:59,800
The whole realm is yours.

92
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,120
Anyone who sings those songs,

93
00:04:03,439 --> 00:04:04,680
kill them.

94
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:09,639
I have

95
00:04:09,639 --> 00:04:12,680
prepared something new tonight.

96
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,800
I'm sure

97
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,199
Your Majesty will love it.

98
00:04:28,279 --> 00:04:29,680
Thank you, My Lord, for saving us.

99
00:04:29,879 --> 00:04:30,759
If not for you,

100
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:32,920
we would have been dead by now.

101
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,920
Yes, My Lord.

102
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,519
My Lord,

103
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:36,319
your scheme was brilliant.

104
00:04:36,319 --> 00:04:37,040
Who would have thought

105
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,199
a few simple songs

106
00:04:38,199 --> 00:04:39,879
could shake Zhu Yunqi's authority?

107
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:42,759
Here.

108
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:43,480
Take this.

109
00:04:45,040 --> 00:04:46,199
Now leave this place

110
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:48,040
and start your lives anew.

111
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,680
- Thank you, My Lord.
- Thank you, My Lord.

112
00:04:51,439 --> 00:04:52,759
How did you manage

113
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:55,439
to get them off the execution ground?

114
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:56,639
Holy Maiden.

115
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:58,079
You wouldn't know this,

116
00:04:58,079 --> 00:04:59,120
but our Nanfeng Pavilion,

117
00:04:59,120 --> 00:05:00,680
on the surface, is a place of pleasure,

118
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,360
but in truth,

119
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,040
it has spies

120
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,560
scattered across the land.

121
00:05:03,759 --> 00:05:05,120
And the entertainers here?

122
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:07,240
Every one of them is skilled
at passing messages.

123
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,240
To stay under the radar,

124
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:10,120
in their spare time,

125
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,800
they perform as singers.

126
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:13,519
And when duty calls,

127
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:15,160
they cloak themselves in black
and fight for justice.

128
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,839
Spreading a few children's songs

129
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:17,720
is nothing special.

130
00:05:18,959 --> 00:05:19,759
Take, for example,

131
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:22,160
rescuing palace maids who are suffering,

132
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,240
My Lord

133
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,360
saves countless of them

134
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,639
every year.

135
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,160
Are your matters all settled?

136
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,120
Yes, My Lord.

137
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,439
And, Holy Maiden,

138
00:05:29,439 --> 00:05:29,920
I...

139
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,800
Not settled, not settled!

140
00:05:36,279 --> 00:05:37,240
I'll go handle it now.

141
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:38,439
All of you,

142
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:38,879
follow me.

143
00:05:38,879 --> 00:05:39,279
Move!

144
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,279
Go!

145
00:05:54,959 --> 00:05:55,639
The Nanfeng Pavilion

146
00:05:55,639 --> 00:05:57,519
is not what you imagined, is it?

147
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:59,680
And you're not what I imagined either.

148
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,560
I...

149
00:06:49,319 --> 00:06:50,959
There's still something I need to do.

150
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:01,839
My Lord.

151
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:03,240
My Lord.

152
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,160
What was that just now?

153
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,279
Such a perfect opportunity.

154
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,000
It was right there.

155
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,360
So close.

156
00:07:08,639 --> 00:07:10,040
And you let it slip.

157
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,000
How could you even let that

158
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,160
happen?

159
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:15,600
I was wrong.

160
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,199
I shouldn't have pried
into your affairs.

161
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:34,759
My Lord.

162
00:07:34,759 --> 00:07:35,800
This is easily solved.

163
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,040
I have a way.

164
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:47,480
Such bold songs,

165
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:50,199
and you dare sing them in the palace?

166
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,519
This is a grave offense!

167
00:07:52,519 --> 00:07:53,920
Mercy, Your Majesty!

168
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:57,920
Why get so angry, Your Majesty?

169
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:01,199
You know the truth perfectly well.

170
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:02,639
So what if I do?

171
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:05,199
The Nanfeng Pavilion's reach
spans the entire city.

172
00:08:05,879 --> 00:08:07,360
What can I do about it?

173
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,199
Why even resist?

174
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,079
What Your Majesty needs to do

175
00:08:11,079 --> 00:08:12,879
is turn their own tactics

176
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,120
against them.

177
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,279
Zhaohua.

178
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:20,639
Do you have a plan?

179
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,399
Feng Ye.

180
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,559
You asked me to come,

181
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,279
but you're not here.

182
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:40,440
How strange.

183
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,080
Eight years ago,

184
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,440
twelve-year-old Young Master Ruan

185
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,080
had a happy family.

186
00:09:08,399 --> 00:09:09,440
But one day,

187
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:12,440
a general came to his home as a guest

188
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:15,159
and brought annihilation to his family.

189
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:16,799
That night,

190
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:19,200
Rong Xiu led troops to massacre
the Minister's manor.

191
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:20,840
His father,

192
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,240
Minister Ruan, risked everything
to protect him.

193
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:25,440
To save him,

194
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:28,000
his father was killed by the general.

195
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,399
From then on,

196
00:09:30,039 --> 00:09:30,879
the boy's life

197
00:09:30,879 --> 00:09:32,399
was defined by vengeance.

198
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,000
He thought of revenge day and night,

199
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,320
and entering the palace

200
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,639
became his only way.

201
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:40,039
For that,

202
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:42,240
he didn't hesitate to become a eunuch.

203
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,440
But little did he know...

204
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,480
Young Master Ruan.

205
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,240
Rise.

206
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:47,879
You don't need to be made a eunuch.

207
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:49,879
No one will ever know.

208
00:09:50,559 --> 00:09:51,559
Why are you helping me?

209
00:09:51,879 --> 00:09:52,519
I am

210
00:09:52,519 --> 00:09:53,200
Dao Er.

211
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,279
Years ago,

212
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:56,600
I was once indebted to Minister Ruan.

213
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:57,679
Rest assured.

214
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,360
I won't let the Ruan family

215
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:00,519
die out.

216
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:03,120
Good deeds bear good fruit.

217
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,720
One act of kindness from my father

218
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,000
gave me a chance to live.

219
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,320
So,

220
00:10:14,919 --> 00:10:15,559
he

221
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:16,759
was never...

222
00:10:17,679 --> 00:10:18,600
Pleasure.

223
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,720
Jiang Yukui.

224
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,360
Starting today,

225
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:23,720
you are my personal attendant.

226
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:33,120
I've opened the cage door for you.

227
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,279
If you have the courage to fly,

228
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:37,039
you may leave anytime.

229
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:40,240
But if you need a place to take shelter,

230
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:42,279
you may return anytime.

231
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,360
My Lord.

232
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,480
Now is the time.

233
00:10:48,639 --> 00:10:49,320
Go.

234
00:11:16,559 --> 00:11:18,360
I've been thinking lately

235
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,919
that when we first met,

236
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,759
if there had been no scheming
or plotting between us,

237
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,639
would things have been different?

238
00:11:28,919 --> 00:11:30,799
But then I think

239
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,759
we both carry

240
00:11:33,759 --> 00:11:35,159
a debt of blood.

241
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,159
If not for our shared goals,

242
00:11:37,159 --> 00:11:38,840
we would never have met.

243
00:11:40,559 --> 00:11:41,519
There's something

244
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:43,240
I've wanted to tell you for a long time.

245
00:11:44,660 --> 00:11:47,740
♪Bound by precepts,
yet craving worldly desires♪

246
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,440
But I truly don't know

247
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,720
how to say it.

248
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:56,500
♪The Buddha speaks of countless paths♪

249
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,480
So,

250
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,279
I'm resorting to this instead.

251
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,860
♪Trapped within
the space between your brows♪

252
00:12:01,919 --> 00:12:03,679
Let the past stay in the past.

253
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,799
From this day forward,

254
00:12:06,799 --> 00:12:08,519
I will give everything I have

255
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:10,200
to protect you.

256
00:12:10,340 --> 00:12:13,260
♪The six senses cannot cleanse
the dust of the past♪

257
00:12:13,279 --> 00:12:14,240
Will you let me?

258
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:20,220
♪Clinging to one obsession,
adrift in a sea of suffering♪

259
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:23,500
♪I can't forget
the stars in your eyes♪

260
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,279
I understand.

261
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,080
Perhaps it's because...

262
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:33,380
♪Hopelessly bound by love♪

263
00:12:34,300 --> 00:12:37,460
♪The green lamp sheds no light
upon one who entered the path♪

264
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:40,660
♪The six senses cannot cleanse
the dust of the past♪

265
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:44,380
♪In dreams, it's you.
Beyond dreams, no one♪

266
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:47,700
♪Clinging to one obsession,
adrift in a sea of suffering♪

267
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:51,100
♪I can't forget
the stars in your eyes♪

268
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:54,660
♪Our fate had already taken root♪

269
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:57,900
♪In this mortal world, there is only us♪

270
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:01,340
♪Hopelessly bound by love♪

271
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:26,780
♪The moon sinks in the west♪

272
00:13:27,260 --> 00:13:28,700
♪The cold lamp burns low♪

273
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:32,020
♪No one knocks upon
the mountain gate♪

274
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:36,140
♪Snow-white winds and moonlight
touch me first♪

275
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:40,820
♪Pear blossoms fill the courtyard♪

276
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,340
♪Yet love and hate entwine♪

277
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:46,100
♪Bound by precepts,
yet craving worldly desires♪

278
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:50,100
♪Gathering red beans
for half a lifetime♪

279
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:54,420
♪The Buddha speaks of countless paths♪

280
00:13:54,420 --> 00:13:57,980
♪How can one glance spanning ages
save a wandering soul♪

281
00:13:57,980 --> 00:14:00,300
♪Trapped within
the space between your brows♪

282
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:04,500
♪Falling deeper and deeper♪

283
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,580
♪The green lamp sheds no light♪

284
00:14:06,580 --> 00:14:08,100
♪Upon one who entered the path♪

285
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:11,300
♪The six senses cannot cleanse
the dust of the past♪

286
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,620
♪In dreams, it's you♪

287
00:14:13,620 --> 00:14:15,020
♪Beyond dreams, no one♪

288
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:18,340
♪Clinging to one obsession,
adrift in a sea of suffering♪

289
00:14:18,340 --> 00:14:21,740
♪I can't forget the stars in your eyes♪

290
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:25,300
♪Our fate had already taken root♪

291
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:28,540
♪In this mortal world, there is only us♪

292
00:14:28,540 --> 00:14:31,980
♪Hopelessly bound by love♪
